----
[[=]]
++ Dive deep, deep diver.
[[/=]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
@@ @@ @@ @@ [[size 200%]]tha·las·so·pho·bi·a.[[/size]]

@@ @@ @@ @@ /θˌalɐsəfˈə͡ʊbi͡ə/

//noun//

@@ @@ the irrational fear of the ocean or deep bodies of water.
[[/div]]
----
[[=]]
The purpose of this theme is for the Fish Council's Deep Sea Site-72, a collaborative project about an ocean based Foundation facility in the mid-1900s, dedicated to research and containment, ten thousand meters below the surface. Think bathyscaphes, acoustic sonar technology, and copper diving suits you'd see out of //Bioshock//.

Although it's not limited to just that. If you want anything to do with deep sea analog horror, or just underwater vibes in general, you've come to the right place. Slap this theme on it and you're good to go.
[[/=]]
----
[[=]]
+ It's getting so cold and dark.
[[/=]]

-----

[[div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"]]
[[image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/theme%3Athalassophobia-sigma/image]]
[[div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:width:300px;;"]]
Tangled icon. Lost. Irretrievable.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

This is a version of the [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/theme:thalassophobia BHL Thalassophobia Theme] by Fish^12, and it is an extension of [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/theme:penumbra Penumbra] by EstrellaYoshte.

@@ @@
@@ @@
@@ @@
@@ @@
@@ @@

Copy paste this in there to get the theme:

[[div class="code"]]
@@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:thalassophobia-sigma]]@@
[[/div]]

This theme comes with [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:betterfootnotes Better Footnotes] integration, [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:centered-header-sigma-9 Centered Header Sigma].
It also changes [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:classified-bar-woed Classified Bar Woed] to make the text visible on the dark background.

----

You can change the logo, title, subtitle, and, technically, accent color by including the following module after the include for the theme:[[footnote]]I will say however that changing the accent color //will// likely cause it to look way worse, but if you can make it work, go nuts[[/footnote]]

[[code]]
[[module CSS]]
:root {
   --lgurl: url(your url);
   --header-title: "HEADER TITLE";
   --header-subtitle: "header subtitle";
   --accentColor: COLOR;
}
[[/module]]
[[/code]]

[[div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"]]
[[image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/theme%3Athalassophobia-sigma/coppermode]]
[[div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:width:300px;;"]]
**Copper Mode**
Add {{|copper-mode=a}} to the include module to use it.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"]]
[[image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/theme%3Athalassophobia-sigma/copperlinks]]
[[div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:width:300px;;"]]
**Copper Links**
Add {{|copper-links=a}} to the include module to use them.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]


